flood waters fierce winds and hail storms have 
plagued chinas central sichuan province in recent days killing 
more than 50 people and injuring at least 1000 according to an 
official report 
the violent weather also ruined crops disrupted transportation 
and wrecked tens of thousands of homes the china news service said 
in a report appearing today in hong kong newspapers 
gaoxian in southern sichuan more than 1000 miles southwest of 
beijing was hit june 25 with storms that triggered mountain 
torrents and rockmud flows that cut roads and communications the 
report said 
the storm destroyed about 140000 homes and 62600 acres of 
crops in more than 1100 villages in gaoxian the report said 
quoting flood prevention authorities in sichuan 
yaan about 80 miles southwest of the provincial capital of 
chengdu was hit hard by storms friday evening the report said 
more than 16000 acres of crops were destroyed and major roads were 
blocked including the one linking sichuan to tibet it said 
