<TEXT>
discovery moved into the glare of 
spotlights early monday on its longawaited trip to the launch pad 
and a giant step toward americas first space shuttle flight since 
the challenger tragedy 
a flagwaving fourth of july crowd of several hundred space 
workers cheered as the 85ton spaceship edged out of an assembly 
building at 1250 am riding upright on the broad back of a giant 
tracked transporter called a crawler 
the 42mile journey to launch pad 39b was scheduled to take six 
to seven hours attached to discovery were a 154foottall external 
fuel tank and the two 149foot solid fuel booster rockets that will 
hurl the craft into space on a flight scheduled for early september 
as the rollout began kennedy space center director forrest s 
mccartney presented astronaut dave hilmers one of discoverys five 
assigned crew members with an autograph book containing the names 
of 15240 engineers technicians managers secretaries clerical 
workers and other center employees who have labored to return the 
shuttle fleet to flight 
the astronauts will carry the book into orbit with them 
mccartney hilmers and other nasa officials watched the rollout 
from a flagbedecked grandstand outside the assembly building 
the early morning move was planned to avoid thunderstorms and 
lighting which are common during the day this time of the year 
center officials originally said all five of discoverys 
astronauts and nasa administrator james c fletcher would be here 
for the rollout but four of the crew members elected to spend the 
holiday weekend with their families in houston and fletchers 
office said friday he couldnt make it 
the failure of a seal in a booster rocket joint doomed 
challenger 73 seconds after it lifted off on jan 28 1986 all 
seven crew members perished in the massive explosion 
since then the booster has been significantly redesigned and 
tested and hundreds of other modifications have been made to the 
shuttle main engines and other systems 
once at the pad discovery will be readied for a critical july 
24 test of modifications to the three main liquidfuel engines 
with the spaceship bolted firmly to its launch mounts the power 
plant will be ignited for 194 seconds at the end of a practice 
countdown 
the following day one final preflight testfiring of a 
redesigned booster rocket is planned at the morton thiokol plant in 
utah both tests must be passed before discovery is certified for 
flight 
on sunday a test of an intentionally damaged version of the 
shuttle rockets redesigned joint was apparently successful morton 
thiokol said the test was conducted at a plant near brigham city 
utah 
it appears no gas leaked outside the joint in spite of the 
very severe intentional flaws said thiokol spokesman rocky raab 
that has really raised our confidence for the fullscale test 
at the end of the month 
the 1 pm mdt test was performed on a simulator that uses three 
shortened rocket cases two joints and 385 pounds of propellant to 
mimic pressures present during when a fullscale rocket motor is 
fired 
last week nasa announced that it had changed the liftoff date 
from late august to early september because it was taking longer 
than expected to prepare discovery for flight 
hilmers and four other veteran shuttle pilots will be at the 
controls when discovery blasts off to mark what nasa is counting on 
to revive americas manned space program the others are commander 
rick hauck dick covey mike lounge and george nelson 
during their fourday mission the astronauts will deploy a 
communications satellite conduct scientific and technical 
experiments and check out changes made to the orbiter systems 
