conditions in afghanistan and that from the standpoint of 
humanism an amnesty will be applied to them 
the soviet union has listed 312 soldiers missing in action in 
afghanistan 
sukharov said authorities have determined that about one third 
of that number died and that perhaps 200 remain on the territory of 
neighboring pakistan many of those may be prisoners of rebel units 
