supreme soviet the countrys highest executive body wanted to 
refute what he said were rumors in the west that prisoners of war 
and deserters would face severe punishment if they returned to the 
soviet union 
the presidium already has pardoned one soldier who was punished 
for desertion he said 
prisoners of war who return will enjoy in full measure all 
political social and all other rights guaranteed by the 
constitution of the ussr to soviet citizens he said 
the legal official said his country was using all channels to 
obtain the release of our soldiers and bring them back home 
he appealed to the united states pakistan and other countries 
to help soviet soldiers who are on their territory to return home 
the soviet union began pulling its 100000 soldiers out of 
afghanistan on may 15 and units still there awaiting withdrawal 
